[{"location":"references/","page":"References","title":"References","text":"Here we create a full list of formatted references contained in our .bib file using","category":"page"},{"location":"references/","page":"References","title":"References","text":"```@bibliography\n```","category":"page"},{"location":"references/#References","page":"References","title":"References","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"references/","page":"References","title":"References","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"#How-to-use-DocumenterCitations.jl","page":"Home","title":"How to use DocumenterCitations.jl","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"DocumenterCitations.jl uses Bibliography.jl to add support for BibTeX citations and references in documentation pages generated by Documenter.jl.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"DocumenterCitations.jl is still in early development so please open issues if you encounter any bugs or pain points, would like to see a new feature, or if you have any questions.","category":"page"},{"location":"#Installation-instructions","page":"Home","title":"Installation instructions","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"You can install the latest version of DocumenterCitations.jl using the built-in package manager (accessed by pressing ] in the Julia command prompt) to add the package and instantiate/build all dependencies","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"julia>]\n(v1.5) pkg> add DocumenterCitations","category":"page"},{"location":"#Telling-Documenter.jl-about-your-bibliography","page":"Home","title":"Telling Documenter.jl about your bibliography","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"You just need a BibTeX .bib file to get started! Let's call it some_references.bib. You want to create a CitationBibliography and pass it to makedocs:","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"using DocumenterCitations\n\nbib = CitationBibliography(\"some_references.bib\")\nmakedocs(bib, ...)","category":"page"},{"location":"#How-to-get-a-sorted-References-list","page":"Home","title":"How to get a sorted References list","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"In order to get a sorted references list you can pass a additional sorting argument to CitationBibliography().","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"bib = CitationBibliography(\"some_references.bib\", sorting = :nyt)","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"The currently supported sorting orders and their behaviours are managed by Bibliography.sorting_rules.","category":"page"},{"location":"#How-to-cite-references-in-your-documentation","page":"Home","title":"How to cite references in your documentation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"You can now use citations anywhere in your docs!","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Here I cite Mayer2012, a useful article, via [Mayer2012](@cite): H. C. Mayer , R. Krechetnikov  (2012).","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"I also cite useful_proof, a book you might not want to read, with [useful_proof](@cite) Alfred North Whitehead , Bertrand Russell  (1925).","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Some TeX diacritical marks are supported, e.g. Karl Heun  (1900).","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Clicking on the citations takes you to the bibliography.","category":"page"},{"location":"#Example","page":"Home","title":"Example","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"DocumenterCitations.Example","category":"page"},{"location":"#DocumenterCitations.Example","page":"Home","title":"DocumenterCitations.Example","text":"Example\n\nFoo.\n\nH. C. Mayer , R. Krechetnikov  (2012)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"}]
